{
 "cells": [
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "# CG generating function (Gaudin, gl(4))\n\nClebsch-Gordan generating-function machinery for the gl(4) two-site Gaudin model, output irrep `mu` in `[S1,S1,0,0] x [S2,S2,0,0]`.\n\nThe Gaudin ODE solver is copied from `GaudinSolver.wb` (this same `Clean/` folder), with the two input reps relabelled **`S` -> `S1`, `P` -> `S2`** throughout the public API (`irreps`, `degQ`, `GaudinSolve`, `BuildQs`). The solver was verified there; only the argument names changed here, and the copy is re-validated at the bottom (worst ODE residual = 0). Sites fixed at $w_1=0,\\,w_2=1$.\n\nOn top of the solver this notebook adds **`Q12[S1,S2,mu]`**, the Wronskian of the first two Q-functions `Q1,Q2` (needed together with the `FastQ.wb` residue primitives).",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## Tensor-product decomposition `[S1,S1,0,0] x [S2,S2,0,0]`\n\ngl(4) character of irrep `lam` is the Schur polynomial; the irreps in the tensor product are those in the product's Schur expansion (peel off the lex-highest monomial with its multiplicity). `irreps[S1,S2]` lists the output irreps `mu`.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[schur, tensorDecomp, dimGL4, irreps];\n\n(*schur polynomial in x[1],x[2],x[3],x[4]*)\nschur[lam_, x_List] := Cancel[Det[Table[x[[i]]^(lam[[j]] + Length[x] - j), {i, Length[x]}, {j, Length[x]}]]/Det[Table[x[[i]]^(Length[x] - j), {i, Length[x]}, {j, Length[x]}]]];\n\n(*dimension of the representation lam = {λ1,λ2,λ3,λ4}*)\ndimGL4[lam_] := Product[(lam[[i]] - lam[[j]] + j - i)/(j - i), {i, 4}, {j, i + 1, 4}];\n\n(*decompose the tensor product λ x μ into irreps*)\ntensorDecomp[lam_, mu_] := Module[{x = Array[xx, 4], prod, rules, nu, mult, out = {}},\n   prod = Expand[schur[lam, x] schur[mu, x]];\n   While[prod =!= 0, rules = Association[CoefficientRules[prod, x]]; nu = Last[Sort[Keys[rules]]];\n     mult = rules[nu]; AppendTo[out, nu -> mult]; prod = Expand[prod - mult schur[nu, x]]];\n   out];\n\n(* the irreps mu (all multiplicity 1 for this family) appearing in [S1,S1,0,0] x [S2,S2,0,0] *)\nirreps[S1_, S2_] := tensorDecomp[{S1, S1, 0, 0}, {S2, S2, 0, 0}][[All, 1]];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* --- Casimir eigenvalues on the output irrep mu, and the Q-polynomial degrees ---\n   Column-ordered generating function (Kazakov et al conventions): G4[u] = Prod_i (u - h(mu_i+4-i)),\n   whose coefficients are the Casimirs. Eigenvalues are symmetric functions of the centered\n   shifted weights xw_i = mu_i + 5/2 - i (= mu_i + rho_i); Pw_k = Sum_i xw_i^k. *)\nClearAll[muhat, xw, Pw, Cas2, Cas4, degQ];\nmuhat[mu_] := Table[mu[[i]] + 4 - i, {i, 4}];\nxw[mu_] := Table[mu[[i]] + 5/2 - i, {i, 4}];\nPw[mu_, k_] := Total[xw[mu]^k];\nCas2[mu_] := Pw[mu, 2] - 5;\nCas4[mu_] := Pw[mu, 4] + 4 Pw[mu, 3] - Pw[mu, 1] Pw[mu, 2] + Pw[mu, 2]/2 - 2 Pw[mu, 1]^2 - 10 Pw[mu, 1] - 51/4;\n(* the SAME shifted weights fix the Q-degrees: deg q_k = (S1+S2+3) - muhat_k = (S1+S2) - mu_k + (k-1)\n   -- convention: arguments always ordered (S1,S2,mu) *)\ndegQ[S1_, S2_, mu_] := Table[(S1 + S2 + 3) - muhat[mu][[k]], {k, 4}]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* --- Gaudin ODE ---\n   Q'''' coefficient is 8(z-w1)^2(z-w2)^2 -- double singular points at the two Gaudin sites, as\n   expected. C2,C4 are the abstract Casimirs of the output irrep mu. The rep-label placeholders\n   S,P in this template are internal dummies, kept distinct from the solver arguments S1,S2 so that\n   Module-localization inside GaudinSolve does not collide with them; GaudinSolve substitutes\n   S->S1, P->S2. So S1,S2 label the two input reps [S1,S1,0,0],[S2,S2,0,0]. *)\nClearAll[gaudinODE];\ngaudinODE = (2*C2 + C2^2 - 2*C4 + 24*P + 2*C2*P + 20*P^2 + 4*P^3 + 24*S + 2*C2*S + 40*P*S + 12*P^2*S + 20*S^2 + 12*P*S^2 + 4*S^3)*Q[z]\n   + 4*(C2 - 4*P - 2*P^2 - 4*S - 4*P*S - 2*S^2)*(2*z + P*z + S*z - w1 - P*w1 - w2 - S*w2)*Derivative[1][Q][z]\n   - 4*(C2*z^2 - 6*P*z^2 - 4*P^2*z^2 - 6*S*z^2 - 8*P*S*z^2 - 4*S^2*z^2 - C2*z*w1 + 8*P*z*w1 + 6*P^2*z*w1 + 4*S*z*w1 + 8*P*S*z*w1\n      + 2*S^2*z*w1 - 2*P*w1^2 - 2*P^2*w1^2 - C2*z*w2 + 4*P*z*w2 + 2*P^2*z*w2 + 8*S*z*w2 + 8*P*S*z*w2 + 6*S^2*z*w2\n      + C2*w1*w2 - 4*P*w1*w2 - 2*P^2*w1*w2 - 4*S*w1*w2 - 8*P*S*w1*w2 - 2*S^2*w1*w2 - 2*S*w2^2 - 2*S^2*w2^2)*Derivative[2][Q][z]\n   - 16*(z - w1)*(z - w2)*(P*z + S*z - P*w1 - S*w2)*Derivative[3][Q][z]\n   + 8*(z - w1)^2*(z - w2)^2*Derivative[4][Q][z];\n(* punctures fixed at w1=0, w2=1 for this solver *)\nwsub = {w1 -> 0, w2 -> 1};",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* --- Gaudin ODE solver ---\n   Arguments always ordered (S1,S2,mu): S1,S2 label the two input reps [S1,S1,0,0],[S2,S2,0,0]; mu\n   is the output irrep. Solves the 4th-order Gaudin ODE for the four polynomial Q's of degrees\n   degQ[S1,S2,mu], returned as monic coefficient lists (coeffs of z^0,z^1,...,z^m). Optional kmax\n   (default 4) returns only the first kmax Q's -- Q12/det1 need just Q1,Q2, and the higher Q's carry\n   the largest degrees, so kmax=2 is much cheaper. GAUGE FIXING: the four Q-degrees are strictly\n   increasing, so any lower-degree solution can be added to a higher one (q_k -> q_k + c q_j, j<k);\n   removed by forcing the coefficient of z^(deg q_j) in q_k to vanish for every j<k.\n   The unknown coefficients enter the ODE linearly, so we build the (numeric, rational) coefficient\n   matrix and LinearSolve it -- faster than a symbolic Solve. cq[m]=1 (monic) and the gauge coeffs=0\n   are imposed by dropping those columns (the monic one is moved to the right-hand side). *)\nClearAll[GaudinSolve];\nGaudinSolve[S1_, S2_, mu_] := GaudinSolve[S1, S2, mu, 4];\nGaudinSolve[S1_, S2_, mu_, kmax_] := Module[{ds, ode},\n   ds = degQ[S1, S2, mu];\n   ode = gaudinODE /. {C2 -> Cas2[mu], C4 -> Cas4[mu], S -> S1, P -> S2} /. wsub;\n   Table[Module[{m = ds[[kk]], gauge = ds[[1 ;; kk - 1]], cvars, cl, mat, freeidx, cvals},\n       cvars = Table[cq[j], {j, 0, m}];\n       cvals = ConstantArray[0, m + 1]; cvals[[m + 1]] = 1;   (* cq[m]=1 monic; gauge coeffs stay 0 *)\n       freeidx = Complement[Range[0, m], Append[gauge, m]];   (* 0-based indices of the free coeffs *)\n       If[freeidx =!= {},\n         cl = CoefficientList[Expand[ode /. Q -> Function[x, (cvars . Table[z^j, {j, 0, m}]) /. z -> x]], z];\n         mat = CoefficientArrays[cl, cvars][[2]];              (* cl == mat . cvars, homogeneous *)\n         MapThread[(cvals[[#1 + 1]] = #2) &, {freeidx, LinearSolve[mat[[All, freeidx + 1]], -mat[[All, m + 1]]]}]];\n       cvals], {kk, kmax}]];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* --- BuildQs: same argument convention as GaudinSolve, (S1,S2,mu[,kmax]), but returns the Q's\n   as explicit polynomials in z (rather than coefficient lists). kmax (default 4) limits to the\n   first kmax Q's. *)\nClearAll[BuildQs];\nBuildQs[S1_, S2_, mu_] := BuildQs[S1, S2, mu, 4];\nBuildQs[S1_, S2_, mu_, kmax_] := Module[{ds = degQ[S1, S2, mu], coeffs = GaudinSolve[S1, S2, mu, kmax]},\n   Table[Sum[coeffs[[kk, j + 1]] z^j, {j, 0, ds[[kk]]}], {kk, kmax}]];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## `Q12` -- Wronskian of `Q1`, `Q2`\n\nTwo-index Q-function `Q12 = Wronskian[{Q1,Q2}, z] = Q1 Q2' - Q2 Q1'`, a polynomial in `z`, degree `deg Q1 + deg Q2 - 1`. Same argument convention `(S1,S2,mu)`.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* Q12 = Wronskian of Q1,Q2 only, so build just those (kmax=2) -- skips the higher-degree Q3,Q4 solves. *)\nClearAll[Q12];\nQ12[S1_, S2_, mu_] := Expand[Wronskian[BuildQs[S1, S2, mu, 2], z]];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## Residue primitives (adapted from `FastQ.wb`, in the spectral variable `z`)\n\nMeasure `1/(z^(2 S1) (z-1)^(2 S2))`. For a polynomial `f(z)`, the residue of `e^{w z} f(z)` against this measure is\n`br[a][e^{w z} f]` = residue at `z=a`, in closed form (Laguerre): `doRes0` (a=0, pole order `2 S1`), `doRes1` (a=1, pole order `2 S2`). `res0`/`res1` are the single-monomial `z^n` residues (closed forms in `w`, they carry no `z` themselves); validated in `FastQ.wb` against direct `Residue` (mismatches = 0). Everything here is in `z` -- the same variable as `Q12` -- so no `z <-> u` substitution is needed.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[mm, res1, res0];\nmm[z_, n_, S1_, S2_, w_] := Exp[w z] z^n / (z^(2 S1) (z - 1)^(2 S2));\n(* res0/res1 memoized (f[x_]:=f[x]=...): for a fixed (S1,S2) sweep they are identical for every mu,\n   and each is a symbolic LaguerreL in w, so caching avoids recomputing them per mu. The ClearAll\n   above clears the cache on re-run -- do re-run this cell if you ever change the measure/formulas. *)\nres1[n_, S1_, S2_] := res1[n, S1, S2] = Exp[w] LaguerreL[2 S2 - 1, n - 2 S1 - 2 S2 + 1, -w];\nres0[n_, S1_, S2_] := res0[n, S1, S2] = If[2 S1 > n, (-1)^(2 S1 + 2 S2 - n + 1) LaguerreL[2 S1 - n - 1, 1 - 2 S1 - 2 S2 + n, w], 0];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* br[0][e^{w z} f] = doRes0[S1,S2,f];  br[1][e^{w z} f] = doRes1[S1,S2,f].  f a polynomial in z. *)\ndoRes0[S1_, S2_, f_] := Module[{nmax, coeffs, res},\n  nmax = Exponent[f, z];\n  coeffs = CoefficientList[f, z];\n  res = Plus @@ (coeffs Table[res0[n, S1, S2], {n, 0, nmax}]);\n  res\n  ]\n\ndoRes1[S1_, S2_, f_] := Module[{nmax, coeffs, res},\n  nmax = Exponent[f, z];\n  coeffs = CoefficientList[f, z];\n  res = Plus @@ (coeffs Table[res1[n, S1, S2], {n, 0, nmax}]);\n  res\n  ]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "## `det1` -- 2x2 residue determinant (monic in `w`)\n\n$$\\det{}_1[S_1,S_2,\\mu]=\\frac{(2S_1-1)!\\,(2S_2-1)!}{Q_{12}(0)\\,Q_{12}(1)\\,e^{w}}\\;\\det\\begin{pmatrix} \\mathrm{br}_0[e^{wz}Q_{12}(z)] & \\mathrm{br}_0[e^{wz}\\,z\\,Q_{12}(z)]\\\\ \\mathrm{br}_1[e^{wz}Q_{12}(z)] & \\mathrm{br}_1[e^{wz}\\,z\\,Q_{12}(z)]\\end{pmatrix}$$\n\nwith `q = Q12[S1,S2,mu]` a polynomial in `z`, and `Q12[0]=q/.z->0`, `Q12[1]=q/.z->1`. Left column `f=Q12(z)`, right column `f=z Q12(z)`; top row `br[0]`, bottom row `br[1]`.\n\nThe `br[1]` entries carry a common factor `e^{w}` (from `res1`), which factors out of the determinant and cancels the overall `1/e^{w}`, so the result is a plain **polynomial in `w`** (a generating function) of degree `2(S1+S2)-2`. The implementation strips that `e^{w}` up front (`res1bar = res1/e^{w}`) and `Expand`s a bare polynomial -- much faster than `ExpandAll` against the exponential.\n\n**Monic normalization.** The bare determinant has leading-in-`w` coefficient `1/((2S1-1)!(2S2-1)!)`, the *same for every* `mu` (each residue's top-`w` term is a pure factorial). Multiplying by `(2S1-1)!(2S2-1)!` therefore makes the generating function **monic in `w`** (leading coefficient `1`), and collapses the large factorial denominators.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* det1: the br[1] entries carry a common factor Exp[w] (from res1) that factors out of the 2x2\n   determinant and cancels the overall 1/Exp[w], leaving a plain polynomial in w. Stripping that\n   Exp[w] up front -- res1bar = res1/Exp[w] -- lets us Expand a bare polynomial instead of\n   ExpandAll-ing against the exponential: identical result, ~15x faster at S1=S2=10. res1bar is\n   memoized like res0/res1.\n   MONIC NORMALIZATION: the bare determinant has leading-in-w coefficient 1/((2S1-1)!(2S2-1)!) for\n   every mu (each residue's top-w term is a pure factorial: res0[0] ~ 1/(2S1-1)!, res1bar[n] ~\n   1/(2S2-1)!, and the Q12(0)Q12(1) cancels), so we multiply by (2S1-1)!(2S2-1)! to make the\n   generating function MONIC in w. This also clears the large factorial denominators. *)\nClearAll[det1, res1bar, doRes1bar];\nres1bar[n_, S1_, S2_] := res1bar[n, S1, S2] = LaguerreL[2 S2 - 1, n - 2 S1 - 2 S2 + 1, -w];\ndoRes1bar[S1_, S2_, f_] := Module[{c = CoefficientList[f, z]}, c . Table[res1bar[n, S1, S2], {n, 0, Length[c] - 1}]];\ndet1[S1_, S2_, mu_] := Module[{q = Q12[S1, S2, mu]},\n   Expand[(2 S1 - 1)! (2 S2 - 1)! Det[{{doRes0[S1, S2, q],    doRes0[S1, S2, z q]},\n               {doRes1bar[S1, S2, q], doRes1bar[S1, S2, z q]}}]/(q /. z -> 0)/(q /. z -> 1)]\n   ];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "irr11=irreps[1,1];\nirr22=irreps[2,2];\nirr33=irreps[3,3];\nirr44=irreps[4,4];\nirr55=irreps[5,5];\nirr66=irreps[6,6];\nirr77=irreps[7,7];\nirr88=irreps[8,8];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[irr10]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "irr10=irreps[10,10];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "Table[det1[8,8,mu]//AbsoluteTiming,{mu,irr88}];//AbsoluteTiming",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "irr10=irreps[10,10];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "dimGL4[{8,8,0,0}]^2",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
